0emissions%20result%20from%20the%20manufacturing%20or%20processing%20of%20chemicals%20and%20materials,%20such%20as%20cement,%20steel,%20aluminum,%20ammonia,%20and%20waste%20processing;%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&bull;Transportation%20of%20materials,%20products,%20waste,%20workers,%20and%20passengers:%20these%20emissions%20result%20from%20the%20combustion%20of%20fuels%20in%20mobile%20combustion%20sources%20owned%20or%20controlled%20by%20the%20organization,%20such%20as%20trucks,%20trains,%20ships,%20airplanes,%20buses,%20and%20cars;%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&bull;Fugitive%20emissions:%20these%20are%20emissions%20that%20are%20not%20physically%20controlled%20but%20result%20from%20intentional%20or%20unintentional%20releases%20of%20GHGs.%20These%20can%20include%20equipment%20leaks%20from%20joints,%20seals,%20packing,%20and%20gaskets;%20methane%20emissions%20(e.g.,%20from%20coal%20mines)%20and%20venting;%20HFC%20emissions%20from%20refrigeration%20and%20air%20conditioning%20equipment;%20and%20methane%20leakages%20(e.g.,%20from%20gas%20transport).%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&nbsp;%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EMethodologies%20used%20to%20calculate%20the%20direct%20(Scope%20I)%20GHG%20emissions%20can%20include:%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&bull;%20direct%20measurement%20of%20energy%20source%20consumed%20(coal,%20gas)%20or%20losses%20(refills)%20of%20cooling%20systems%20and%20conversion%20to%20GHG%20(CO2%20equivalents);%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&bull;%20mass%20balance%20calculations;%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&bull;%20calculations%20based%20on%20site-specific%20data,%20such%20as%20for%20fuel%20composition%20analysis;%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&bull;%20calculations%20based%20on%20published%20criteria,%20such%20as%20emission%20factors%20and%20GWP%20rates;%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&bull;%20direct%20measurements%20of%20GHG%20emissions,%20such%20as%20continuous%20online%20analyzers;%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&bull;%20estimations.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EIf%20estimations%20are%20used%20due%20to%20a%20lack%20of%20default%20figures,%20the%20reporting%20organization%20can%20indicate%20the%20basis%20and%20assumptions%20on%20which%20figures%20were%20estimated.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EFor%20recalculations%20of%20prior%20year%20emissions,%20the%20organization%20can%20follow%20the%20approach%20in%20the%20&lsquo;GHG%20Protocol%20Corporate%20Standard&rsquo;.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EThe%20chosen%20emission%20factors%20can%20originate%20from%20mandatory%20reporting%20requirements,%20voluntary%20reporting%20frameworks,%20or%20industry%20groups.%20Estimates%20of%20GWP%20rates%20change%20over%20time%20as%20scientific%20research%20develops.%20GWP%20rates%20from%20the%20Second%20Assessment%20Report%20of%20the%20Intergovernmental%20Panel%20on%20Climate%20Change%20(IPCC)%20are%20used%20as%20the%20basis%20for%20international%20negotiations%20under%20the%20&lsquo;Kyoto%20Protocol&rsquo;.%20Thus,%20such%20rates%20can%20be%20used%20for%20disclosing%20GHG%20emissions%20where%20it%20does%20not%20conflict%20with%20national%20or%20regional%20reporting%20requirements.%20The%20organization%20can%20also%20use%20the%20latest%20GWP%20rates%20from%20the%20most%20recent%20IPCC%20assessment%20report.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EThe%20organization%20can%20combine%20Disclosure%20305-1%20with%20Disclosures%20305-2%20(energy%20indirect/Scope%202%20GHG%20emissions)%20and%20305-3%20(other%20indirect/Scope%203%20GHG%20emissions)%20to%20disclose%20total%20GHG%20emissions.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EFurther%20details%20and%20guidance%20are%20available%20in%20the%20&lsquo;GHG%20Protocol%20Corporate%20Standard&rsquo;.%20See%20also%20references%20%5B1%5D,%20%5B2%5D,%20%5B12%5D,%20%5B13%5D,%20%5B14%5D%20and%20%5B19%5D%20in%20the%20Bibliography.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&nbsp;%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E%3Cstrong%3ECompilation%20requirements%20%3C/strong%3E%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E2.1%20When%20compiling%20the%20information%20specified%20in%20Disclosure%20305-1,%20the%20reporting%20organization%20shall:%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E2.1.1%20exclude%20any%20GHG%20trades%20from%20the%20calculation%20of%20gross%20direct%20(Scope%201)%20GHG%20emissions;%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E2.1.2%20report%20biogenic%20emissions%20of%20CO2%20from%20the%20combustion%20or%20biodegradation%20of%20biomass%20separately%20from%20the%20gross%20direct%20(Scope%201)%20GHG%20emissions.%20Exclude%20biogenic%20emissions%20of%20other%20types%20of%20GHG%20(such%20as%20CH4%20and%20N2O),%20and%20biogenic%20emissions%20of%20CO2%20that%20occur%20in%20the%20life%20cycle%20of%20biomass%20other%20than%20from%20combustion%20or%20biodegradation%20(such%20as%20GHG%20emissions%20from%20processing%20or%20transporting%20biomass).%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&nbsp;%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E%3Cspan%20style=%22font-size:%2012pt;%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EGuidance%20%3Cstrong%20style=%22font-size:%2012pt;%20background-color:%20initial;%22%3E&nbsp;&amp;%20Compilation%20requirement&nbsp;%3C/strong%3E%20for%20Disclosure%20305-2%20%3C/strong%3E%3C/span%3E%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EEnergy%20indirect%20(Scope%202)%20GHG%20emissions%20include,%20but%20are%20not%20limited%20to,%20the%20CO2%20emissions%20from%20the%20generation%20of%20purchased%20or%20acquired%20electricity,%20heating,%20cooling,%20and%20steam%20consumed%20by%20an%20organization%20&ndash;%20disclosed%20as%20specified%20in%20Disclosure%20302-1%20of%20GRI%20302:%20Energy%202016.%20For%20many%20organizations,%20the%20energy%20indirect%20(Scope%202)%20GHG%20emissions%20that%20result%20from%20the%20generation%20of%20purchased%20electricity%20can%20be%20much%20greater%20than%20their%20direct%20(Scope%201)%20GHG%20emissions.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EThe%20&lsquo;GHG%20Protocol%20Scope%202%20Guidance&rsquo;%20requires%20organizations%20to%20provide%20two%20distinct%20Scope%202%20values:%20a%20location-based%20and%20a%20market-based%20value.%20A%20location-based%20method%20reflects%20the%20average%20GHG%20emissions%20intensity%20of%20grids%20on%20which%20energy%20consumption%20occurs,%20using%20mostly%20grid-average%20emission%20factor%20data.%20A%20market-based%20method%20reflects%20emissions%20from%20electricity%20that%20an%20organization%20has%20purposefully%20chosen%20(or%20its%20lack%20of%20choice).%20It%20derives%20emission%20factors%20from%20contractual%20instruments,%20which%20include%20any%20type%20of%20contract%20between%20two%20parties%20for%20the%20sale%20and%20purchase%20of%20energy%20bundled%20with%20attributes%20about%20the%20energy%20generation,%20or%20for%20unbundled%20attribute%20claims.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EThe%20market-based%20method%20calculation%20also%20includes%20the%20use%20of%20a%20residual%20mix,%20if%20the%20organization%20does%20not%20have%20specified%20emissions-intensity%20from%20its%20contractual%20instruments.%20This%20helps%20prevent%20double%20counting%20between%20consumers&rsquo;%20market-based%20method%20figures.%20If%20a%20residual%20mix%20is%20unavailable,%20the%20organization%20can%20disclose%20this%20and%20use%20grid-average%20emission%20factors%20as%20a%20proxy%20(which%20can%20mean%20that%20the%20location-based%20and%20market-based%20are%20the%20same%20number%20until%20information%20on%20the%20residual%20mix%20is%20available).%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EThe%20reporting%20organization%20can%20apply%20the%20Quality%20Criteria%20in%20the%20&lsquo;GHG%20Protocol%20Scope%202%20Guidance&rsquo;%20so%20that%20contractual%20instruments%20convey%20GHG%20emission%20rate%20claims%20and%20to%20prevent%20double%20counting.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EFor%20recalculations%20of%20prior%20year%20emissions,%20the%20organization%20can%20follow%20the%20approach%20in%20the%20&lsquo;GHG%20Protocol%20Corporate%20Standard&rsquo;.%20The%20chosen%20emission%20factors%20can%20originate%20from%20mandatory%20reporting%20requirements,%20voluntary%20reporting%20frameworks,%20or%20industry%20groups.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EEstimates%20of%20GWP%20rates%20change%20over%20time%20as%20scientific%20research%20develops.%20GWP%20rates%20from%20the%20Second%20Assessment%20Report%20of%20the%20IPCC%20are%20used%20as%20the%20basis%20for%20international%20negotiations%20under%20the%20&lsquo;Kyoto%20Protocol&rsquo;.%20Thus,%20such%20rates%20can%20be%20used%20for%20disclosing%20GHG%20emissions%20where%20it%20does%20not%20conflict%20with%20national%20or%20regional%20reporting%20requirements.%20The%20organization%20can%20also%20use%20the%20latest%20GWP%20rates%20from%20the%20most%20recent%20IPCC%20assessment%20report.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EThe%20organization%20can%20combine%20Disclosure%20305-2%20with%20Disclosures%20305-1%20(direct/Scope%201%20GHG%20emissions)%20and%20305-3%20(other%20indirect/Scope%203%20GHG%20emissions)%20to%20disclose%20total%20GHG%20emissions.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EFurther%20details%20and%20guidance%20are%20available%20in%20the%20&lsquo;GHG%20Protocol%20Corporate%20Standard&rsquo;.%20Details%20on%20the%20location-based%20and%20market-based%20methods%20are%20available%20in%20the%20&lsquo;GHG%20Protocol%20Scope%202%20Guidance&rsquo;.&nbsp;%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&nbsp;%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E%3Cstrong%3ECompilation%20requirements%3C/strong%3E%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E2.3%20When%20compiling%20the%20information%20specified%20in%20Disclosure%20305-2,%20the%20reporting%20organization%20shall:%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E2.3.1%20exclude%20any%20GHG%20trades%20from%20the%20calculation%20of%20gross%20energy%20indirect%20(Scope%202)%20GHG%20emissions;%202.3.2%20exclude%20other%20indirect%20(Scope%203)%20GHG%20emissions%20that%20are%20disclosed%20as%20specified%20in%20Disclosure%20305-3;%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E2.3.3%20account%20and%20report%20energy%20indirect%20(Scope%202)%20GHG%20emissions%20based%20on%20the%20location-based%20method,%20if%20it%20has%20operations%20in%20markets%20without%20product%20or%20supplier-specific%20data;%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E2.3.4%20account%20and%20report%20energy%20indirect%20(Scope%202)%20GHG%20emissions%20based%20on%20both%20the%20location-based%20and%20market-based%20methods,%20if%20it%20has%20any%20operations%20in%20markets%20providing%20product%20or%20supplier-specific%20data%20in%20the%20form%20of%20contractual%20instruments.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&nbsp;%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E%3Cspan%20style=%22font-size:%2012pt;%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EGuidance%20%3Cstrong%20style=%22font-size:%2012pt;%20background-color:%20initial;%22%3E&nbsp;&amp;%20Compilation%20requirement&nbsp;%3C/strong%3E%20for%20Disclosure%20305-3%3C/strong%3E%3C/span%3E%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EOther%20indirect%20(Scope%203)%20GHG%20emissions%20are%20a%20consequence%20of%20an%20organization&rsquo;s%20activities,%20but%20occur%20from%20sources%20not%20owned%20or%20controlled%20by%20the%20organization.%20Other%20indirect%20(Scope%203)%20GHG%20emissions%20include%20both%20upstream%20and%20downstream%20emissions.%20Some%20examples%20of%20Scope%203%20activities%20include%20extracting%20and%20producing%20purchased%20materials;%20transporting%20purchased%20fuels%20in%20vehicles%20not%20owned%20or%20controlled%20by%20the%20organization;%20and%20the%20end%20use%20of%20products%20and%20services.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EOther%20indirect%20emissions%20can%20also%20come%20from%20the%20decomposing%20of%20the%20organization&rsquo;s%20waste.%20Process-related%20emissions%20during%20the%20manufacture%20of%20purchased%20goods%20and%20fugitive%20emissions%20in%20facilities%20not%20owned%20by%20the%20organization%20can%20also%20produce%20indirect%20emissions.%20For%20some%20organizations,%20GHG%20emissions%20that%20result%20from%20energy%20consumption%20outside%20of%20the%20organization%20can%20be%20much%20greater%20than%20their%20direct%20(Scope%201)%20or%20energy%20indirect%20(Scope%202)%20GHG%20emissions.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&nbsp;%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EThe%20reporting%20organization%20can%20identify%20other%20indirect%20(Scope%203)%20GHG%20emissions%20by%20assessing%20which%20of%20its%20activities&rsquo;%20emissions:%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&bull;%20Contribute%20significantly%20to%20the%20organization&rsquo;s%20total%20anticipated%20other%20indirect%20(Scope%203)%20GHG%20emissions;%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&bull;%20Offer%20potential%20for%20reductions%20the%20organization%20can%20undertake%20or%20influence;%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&bull;%20Contribute%20to%20climate%20change-related%20risks,%20such%20as%20financial,%20regulatory,%20supply%20chain,%20product%20and%20customer,%20litigation,%20and%20reputational%20risks;%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&bull;%20Are%20deemed%20material%20by%20stakeholders,%20such%20as%20customers,%20suppliers,%20investors,%20or%20civil%20society;%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&bull;%20Result%20from%20outsourced%20activities%20previously%20performed%20in-house,%20or%20that%20are%20typically%20performed%20in-house%20by%20other%20organizations%20in%20the%20same%20sector;%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&bull;%20Have%20been%20identified%20as%20significant%20for%20the%20organization&rsquo;s%20sector;%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&bull;%20meet%20any%20additional%20criteria%20for%20determining%20relevance,%20developed%20by%20the%20organization%20or%20by%20organizations%20in%20its%20sector.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EThe%20organization%20can%20use%20the%20following%20upstream%20and%20downstream%20categories%20and%20activities%20from%20the%20&lsquo;GHG%20Protocol%20Corporate%20Value%20Chain%20Standard&rsquo;.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&nbsp;%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EUpstream%20categories%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E1.%20Purchased%20goods%20and%20services%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E2.%20Capital%20goods%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E3.%20Fuel-%20and%20energy-related%20activities%20(not%20included%20in%20Scope%201%20or%20Scope%202)%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E4.%20Upstream%20transportation%20and%20distribution%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E5.%20Waste%20generated%20in%20operations%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E6.%20Business%20travel%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E7.%20Employee%20commuting%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E8.%20Upstream%20leased%20assets%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EOther%20upstream%20Downstream%20categories&nbsp;%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E9.%20Downstream%20transportation%20and%20distribution%2010.%20Processing%20of%20sold%20products%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E11.%20Use%20of%20sold%20products%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E12.%20End-of-life%20treatment%20of%20sold%20products%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E13.%20Downstream%20leased%20assets%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E14.%20Franchises%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E15.%20Investments%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&nbsp;%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EOther%20downstream%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EFor%20each%20of%20these%20categories%20and%20activities,%20the%20organization%20can%20provide%20a%20figure%20in%20CO2%20equivalent%20or%20explain%20why%20certain%20data%20are%20not%20included.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EFor%20recalculations%20of%20prior%20year%20emissions,%20the%20organization%20can%20follow%20the%20approach%20in%20the%20&lsquo;GHG%20Protocol%20Corporate%20Value%20Chain%20Standard&rsquo;.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EThe%20chosen%20emission%20factors%20can%20originate%20from%20mandatory%20reporting%20requirements,%20voluntary%20reporting%20frameworks,%20or%20industry%20groups.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EEstimates%20of%20GWP%20rates%20change%20over%20time%20as%20scientific%20research%20develops.%20GWP%20rates%20from%20the%20Second%20Assessment%20Report%20of%20the%20IPCC%20are%20used%20as%20the%20basis%20for%20international%20negotiations%20under%20the%20&lsquo;Kyoto%20Protocol&rsquo;.%20Thus,%20such%20rates%20can%20be%20used%20for%20disclosing%20GHG%20emissions%20where%20it%20does%20not%20conflict%20with%20national%20or%20regional%20reporting%20requirements.&nbsp;The%20organization%20can%20also%20use%20the%20latest%20GWP%20rates%20from%20the%20most%20recent%20IPCC%20assessment%20report.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EThe%20organization%20can%20combine%20Disclosure%20305-3%20with%20Disclosures%20305-1%20(direct/Scope%201%20GHG%20emissions)%20and%20305-2%20(energy%20indirect/Scope%202%20GHG%20emissions)%20to%20disclose%20total%20GHG%20emissions.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&nbsp;%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E%3Cstrong%3ECompilation%20requirements%3C/strong%3E%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E2.5%20When%20compiling%20the%20information%20specified%20in%20Disclosure%20305-3,%20the%20reporting%20organization%20shall:%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E2.5.1%20exclude%20any%20GHG%20trades%20from%20the%20calculation%20of%20gross%20other%20indirect%20(Scope%203)%20GHG%20emissions;%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E2.5.2%20exclude%20energy%20indirect%20(Scope%202)%20GHG%20emissions%20from%20this%20disclosure.%20Energy%20indirect%20(Scope%202)%20GHG%20emissions%20are%20disclosed%20as%20specified%20in%20Disclosure%20305-2;%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E2.5.3%20report%20biogenic%20emissions%20of%20CO2%20from%20the%20combustion%20or%20biodegradation%20of%20biomass%20that%20occur%20in%20its%20value%20chain%20separately%20from%20the%20gross%20other%20indirect%20(Scope%203)%20GHG%20emissions.%20Exclude%20biogenic%20emissions%20of%20other%20types%20of%20GHG%20(such%20as%20CH4%20and%20N2O),%20and%20biogenic%20emissions%20of%20CO2%20that%20occur%20in%20the%20life%20cycle%20of%20biomass%20other%20than%20from%20combustion%20or%20biodegradation%20(such%20as%20GHG%20emissions%20from%20processing%20or%20transporting%20biomass).%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&nbsp;%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E%3Cspan%20style=%22font-size:%2012pt;%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EGuidance%20%3Cstrong%20style=%22font-size:%2012pt;%20background-color:%20initial;%22%3E&nbsp;&amp;%20Compilation%20requirement&nbsp;%3C/strong%3E%20for%20Disclosure%20305-4%20%3C/strong%3E%3C/span%3E%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EIntensity%20ratios%20can%20be%20provided%20for,%20among%20others:%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&bull;%20Products%20(such%20as%20metric%20tons%20of%20CO2%20emissions%20per%20unit%20produced);%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&bull;%20Services%20(such%20as%20metric%20tons%20of%20CO2%20emissions%20per%20function%20or%20per%20service);%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&bull;%20Sales%20(such%20as%20metric%20tons%20of%20CO2%20emissions%20per%20sales).%20Organization-specific%20metrics%20(denominators)%20can%20include:%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&bull;%20Units%20of%20product;%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&bull;%20Production%20volume%20(such%20as%20metric%20tons,%20liters,%20or%20MWh);%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&bull;%20Size%20(such%20as%20m2%20floor%20space);%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&bull;%20Number%20of%20full-time%20employees;%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&bull;%20Monetary%20units%20(such%20as%20revenue%20or%20sales).%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EThe%20reporting%20organization%20can%20report%20an%20intensity%20ratio%20for%20direct%20(Scope%201)%20and%20energy%20indirect%20(Scope%202)%20GHG%20emissions%20combined,%20using%20the%20figures%20reported%20in%20Disclosures%20305-1%20and%20305-2.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&nbsp;%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E%3Cstrong%3ECompilation%20requirements%20%3C/strong%3E%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E2.7%20When%20compiling%20the%20information%20specified%20in%20Disclosure%20305-4,%20the%20reporting%20organization%20shall:%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E2.7.1%20calculate%20the%20ratio%20by%20dividing%20the%20absolute%20GHG%20emissions%20(the%20numerator)%20by%20the%20organization-specific%20metric%20(the%20denominator);%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E2.7.2%20if%20reporting%20an%20intensity%20ratio%20for%20other%20indirect%20(Scope%203)%20GHG%20emissions,%20report%20this%20intensity%20ratio%20separately%20from%20the%20intensity%20ratios%20for%20direct%20(Scope%201)%20and%20energy%20indirect%20(Scope%202)%20emissions.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&nbsp;%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E%3Cstrong%3E%20Background%20%3C/strong%3E%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EIntensity%20ratios%20define%20GHG%20emissions%20in%20the%20context%20of%20an%20organization-specific%20metric.%20Many%20organizations%20track%20environmental%20performance%20with%20intensity%20ratios,%20which%20are%20often%20called%20normalized%20environmental%20impact%20data.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EGHG%20emissions%20intensity%20expresses%20the%20amount%20of%20GHG%20emissions%20per%20unit%20of%20activity,%20output,%20or%20any%20other%20organization-specific%20metric.%20In%20combination%20with%20an%20organization&rsquo;s%20absolute%20GHG%20emissions,%20reported%20in%20Disclosures%20305-1,%20305-2,%20and%20305-3,%20GHG%20emissions%20intensity%20helps%20to%20contextualize%20the%20organization&rsquo;s%20efficiency,%20including%20in%20relation%20to%20other%20organizations.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&nbsp;%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E%3Cspan%20style=%22font-size:%2012pt;%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EGuidance%20%3Cstrong%20style=%22font-size:%2012pt;%20background-color:%20initial;%22%3E&nbsp;&amp;%20Compilation%20requirement&nbsp;%3C/strong%3E%20for%20Disclosure%20305-5%20%3C/strong%3E%3C/span%3E%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EThe%20reporting%20organization%20can%20prioritize%20disclosing%20reduction%20initiatives%20that%20were%20implemented%20in%20the%20reporting%20period,%20and%20that%20have%20the%20potential%20to%20contribute%20significantly%20to%20reductions.%20The%20organization%20can%20describe%20reduction%20initiatives%20and%20their%20targets%20when%20reporting%20how%20it%20manages%20this%20topic.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EReduction%20initiatives%20can%20include:%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&bull;%20process%20redesign;%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&bull;%20conversion%20and%20retrofitting%20of%20equipment;%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&bull;%20fuel%20switching;%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&bull;%20changes%20in%20behavior;%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&bull;%20offsets.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EThe%20organization%20can%20report%20reductions%20disaggregated%20by%20initiatives%20or%20groups%20of%20initiatives.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EThis%20disclosure%20can%20be%20used%20in%20combination%20with%20Disclosures%20305-1,%20305-2,%20and%20305-3%20of%20this%20Standard%20to%20monitor%20the%20reduction%20of%20GHG%20emissions%20with%20reference%20to%20the%20organization&rsquo;s%20targets,%20or%20to%20regulations%20and%20trading%20systems%20at%20international%20or%20national%20level.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&nbsp;%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E%3Cstrong%3ECompilation%20requirements%20%3C/strong%3E%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E2.9%20When%20compiling%20the%20information%20specified%20in%20Disclosure%20305-5,%20the%20reporting%20organization%20shall:%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E2.9.1%20exclude%20reductions%20resulting%20from%20reduced%20production%20capacity%20or%20outsourcing;%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E2.9.2%20use%20the%20inventory%20or%20project%20method%20to%20account%20for%20reductions;%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E2.9.3%20calculate%20an%20initiative&rsquo;s%20total%20reductions%20of%20GHG%20emissions%20as%20the%20sum%20of%20its%20associated%20primary%20effects%20and%20any%20significant%20secondary%20effects;%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E2.9.4%20if%20reporting%20two%20or%20more%20Scope%20types,%20report%20the%20reductions%20for%20each%20separately;%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E2.9.5%20report%20reductions%20from%20offsets%20separately.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&nbsp;%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E%3Cstrong%3EGuidance%20for%20clause%202.9.2%3C/strong%3E%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EThe%20inventory%20method%20compares%20reductions%20to%20a%20base%20year.%20The%20project%20method%20compares%20reductions%20to%20a%20baseline.%20Further%20details%20on%20these%20methods%20are%20available%20in%20references%20%5B15%5D%20and%20%5B16%5D%20in%20the%20Bibliography.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&nbsp;%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E%3Cstrong%3EGuidance%20for%20clause%202.9.3%3C/strong%3E%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EPrimary%20effects%20are%20the%20elements%20or%20activities%20designed%20to%20reduce%20GHG%20emissions,%20such%20as%20carbon%20storage.%20Secondary%20effects%20are%20smaller,%20unintended%20consequences%20of%20a%20reduction%20initiative,%20including%20changes%20to%20production%20or%20manufacture,%20which%20result%20in%20changes%20to%20GHG%20emissions%20elsewhere.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&nbsp;%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E%3Cspan%20style=%22font-size:%2012pt;%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EGuidance%20%3Cstrong%20style=%22font-size:%2012pt;%20background-color:%20initial;%22%3E&nbsp;&amp;%20Compilation%20requirement&nbsp;%3C/strong%3E%20for%20Disclosure%20305-6%20%3C/strong%3E%3C/span%3E%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EThe%20reporting%20organization%20can%20report%20separate%20or%20combined%20data%20for%20the%20substances%20included%20in%20the%20calculation.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&nbsp;%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E%3Cstrong%3ECompilation%20requirements%3C/strong%3E%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E2.11%20When%20compiling%20the%20information%20specified%20in%20Disclosure%20305-6,%20the%20reporting%20organization%20shall:%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E2.11.1%20calculate%20the%20production%20of%20ODS%20as%20the%20amount%20of%20ODS%20produced,%20minus%20the%20amount%20destroyed%20by%20approved%20technologies,%20and%20minus%20the%20amount%20entirely%20used%20as%20feedstock%20in%20the%20manufacture%20of%20other%20chemicals;%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&nbsp;%20%5BProduction%20of%20ODS%20=%20ODS%20produced%20-%20ODS%20destroyed%20by%20approved%20technologies%20-%20ODS%20entirely%20used%20as%20feedstock%20in%20the%20manufacture%20of%20other%20chemicals%5D%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E2.11.2%20exclude%20ODS%20recycled%20and%20reused.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&nbsp;%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E%3Cstrong%3E%20Background%20%3C/strong%3E%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EMeasuring%20ODS%20production,%20imports,%20and%20exports%20helps%20to%20indicate%20how%20an%20organization%20complies%20with%20legislation.%20This%20is%20particularly%20relevant%20if%20the%20organization%20produces%20or%20uses%20ODS%20in%20its%20processes,%20products%20and%20services%20and%20is%20subject%20to%20phase-out%20commitments.%20Results%20on%20ODS%20phase-out%20help%20to%20indicate%20the%20organization&rsquo;s%20position%20in%20any%20markets%20affected%20by%20regulation%20on%20ODS.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EThis%20disclosure%20covers%20the%20substances%20included%20in%20Annexes%20A,%20B,%20C,%20and%20E%20of%20the%20&lsquo;Montreal%20Protocol&rsquo;%20as%20well%20as%20any%20other%20ODS%20produced,%20imported,%20or%20exported%20by%20an%20organization.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&nbsp;%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E%3Cspan%20style=%22font-size:%2012pt;%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cstrong%20style=%22font-size:%2012pt;%20background-color:%20initial;%22%3ECompilation%20requirement&nbsp;%3C/strong%3E%20for%20Disclosure%20305-7%3C/strong%3E%3C/span%3E%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cspan%20style=%22font-size:%2010pt;%22%3ECompilation%20requirements%20%3C/span%3E%3C/strong%3E%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cd